TWIN CORE: The Federated Backbone of the Digital Twin
The Vision
At BNP Paribas, resolving complex IT issues requires more than isolated local tools: it demands a systemic understanding and the cooperation of multiple areas of expertise.

Knowledge is fragmented.

Creating effective AI agents from scratch is too slow and costly.

Local intelligences (domains) struggle to collaborate with each other.
==> The IT environment lacks a federated backbone to unite these areas of expertise.

Twin Core is the philosophy and the unifying foundation of the Digital Twin. It is a Variable Geometry ecosystem that provides the accelerators (Knowledge Graphs, Knowledge Bases, Agentic Platform) enabling franchises to build, orchestrate their agents, and solve their Use Cases massively faster.

The Problem
Business domains (Security, Infrastructure, Change) want to deploy AI but face a technological barrier. We are facing:

The complexity of linking business documentation to technical reality.

The "blank page" syndrome: recreating platforms, data access, and orchestrators for every new project.

The inability to handle cross-functional incidents (e.g., an issue involving Security, Network, and Change simultaneously).

The extreme difficulty of developing advanced AI algorithms in isolation.

The Solution: Twin Core
Twin Core = Knowledge Fabric (KG/KB) + Agentic Platform + Advanced AI Solutions
Operating in a "Franchisor" logic, Twin Core provides the state-of-the-art equipment and engines to facilitate access to knowledge and accelerate the creation of local agents:

1. The "Platform" Assets (Tools, Facilitators & Cooperation Hub):

Knowledge Graph (KG) Platform: Provided "As-a-Service," this includes the central graph database and industrialized ingestion pipelines to seamlessly query the IT topology and Golden Events.

Knowledge Base (KB) Platform: An advanced GraphRAG architecture (combining Vector search and Graph databases) enabling franchises to easily transform unstructured documentation into actionable, semantic knowledge.

Agentic Platform & Central Registry: The mandatory hosting environment and central catalog to register local Skills. It offers a premium DevX (Developer Experience) with Coding Agents leveraging the SDD (Specification Driven Development) methodology to accelerate the build phase.

2. The "AI" Assets (Complex Engines & Cognitive Frameworks):

Ready-to-deploy Cognitive Engines: We abstract the deep, centralized R&D complexity required for systemic AI (such as Graph Neural Networks) into turnkey solutions. The first active release is the "Correlation Engine" (dynamically bridging Incidents and Changes).

Neurosymbolic AI & Systemic Modeling: We build complex AI solutions blending the logical reasoning of the Graph (rules, Jurisdiction) with the power of LLMs to simulate IT behavior, paving the way for our future World Model.

Cross-domain Orchestration Frameworks: AI routing patterns (The Router, The Synthesizer) designed to break down complex Use Cases and intelligently query the local data of the franchises.

Twin Core is NOT a simple Chatbot, nor an isolated LLM. It is:

The Orchestrator of Collective Intelligence: Where a chatbot answers simple questions, Twin Core makes dozens of specialized agents cooperate to solve systemic problems.

A Neurosymbolic Engine: A simple LLM hallucinates; Twin Core anchors AI in the mathematical and topological reality of the IT system via the Knowledge Graph.

An Agentic Production Factory: It doesn't just deliver a conversational interface; it provides franchises (via Variable Geometry) with the tools to build their own AIs and plug them into the IT ecosystem.

"Twin Core does not centralize data; it orchestrates the cooperation of intelligences to solve complex IT problems."

Twin Core halves the technological effort required by a franchise to launch its first agentic use cases.
